&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank HCA for Student Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you currently a student nurse? Joining the nurse bank as an HCA can be a great way to gain valuable knowledge and experience in acute clinical areas and give you the opportunity to work flexibly around your studies. As a bank HCA, you will be working across our adult inpatient wards or the outpatients department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The other benefits to working on the nurse bank are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First choice of available shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid annual leave entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enrolment in the NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for this role, you must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be studying at University for a Registered Nurse qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have started your first clinical placement which must be within an acute hospital setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a reliable and self-motivated individual with excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the ability to adapt to changing situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you fit the above specification, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*** IMPORTANT NOTES FOR APPLICANTS ***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please put the contact details of your placement mentor and a Uni tutor as your referees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All other students (mental health, paramedic science etc or those studying health and social care at college) should apply to our healthcare assistant advert (job ref. 428-ATR8600)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be advised that if they are successful in obtaining a position, they will be required to provide the following on their occupational health form:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documented evidence of dates of 2 MMR Vaccinations and or serology (blood test) confirming immunity to Measles and Rubella &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Confirmation of a history of Varicella (Chickenpox Infection) and /or having 2 Varicella Vaccination or evidence of a or serology (blood test ) confirming immunity to Varicella (Chickenpox)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If candidates are not coming from any countries known to be high risk for TB before entering the UK, further tests and update for TB /BCG vaccination and Hepatitis B vaccination can be done and commenced when they arrive and their clearance will not be dependent on this initially, as long as they can provide requested evidence for the first 2 points above.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 30/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Temporary staffing office: temporary.staffingoffice@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel. 0300 019 2183&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Randall: emma.randall@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
